By default, one EBS volume can only attach to one EC2 instance at a time. But with Multi-Attach (available only on io1/io2), 
you can attach the same EBS volume to multiple EC2 instances simultaneously within the same Availability Zone.

💡 Use Cases:
1. Higher Application Availability:
      Used in clustered Linux applications
      Example: Teradata
      Multiple instances can read and write simultaneously
2. Concurrent Write Operations:
    Applications must be able to manage concurrent writes
    The application itself is responsible for handling conflicts

              Availability Zone 1
          ┌─────────────────────────────┐
          │                             │
          │  EC2        EC2        EC2  │
          │  Instance   Instance   Instance│
          │    │          │          │  │
          │    └──────────┴──────────┘  │
          │               │             │
          │         io2 EBS Volume      │
          │        (Multi-Attach) ✅    │
          └─────────────────────────────┘
